                            <comment id="312783" author="adilger" created="Tue, 14 Sep 2021 19:46:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That happens if you run the script with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;sh sanity.sh&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (note &lt;tt&gt;sh&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;bash&lt;/tt&gt;), or your &lt;tt&gt;sh&lt;/tt&gt; is not actually &lt;tt&gt;bash&lt;/tt&gt;.  The script itself has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
#!/bin/bash
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;at the start since commit 0.0.0-1885-g0959449a99 in 2002-11-02, so &lt;tt&gt;./sanity.sh&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; result in it being interpreted by bash...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
